OL,6,FAnalysis commissioned by the DfT found
OL,7,Fkeeping the cap at #2 was "not
OL,8,Ffinancially sustainable for the
OL,9,Ftaxpayer" and "offered poor value for
OL,10,Fmoney", the source added.
OL,12,FLocal transport authorities have the
OL,13,Fpower to keep the cap lower in their
OL,14,Fareas if they subsidise it themselves,
OL,15,For fund their own local schemes.
OL,17,FGreater Manchester Mayor Andy Burnham
OL,18,Fpreviously announced that single fares
OL,19,Fin the region will remain capped at #2
OL,20,F"for the whole of 2025 but subject to
OL,21,Fa mid-year review".
